#-Function--msg.sys
  Function: msg.sys
      Desc: output an informational message, with option to write to systemd journal.
  Synopsis: msg.sys [log] string [string ...]
          : 	'log'		if specified, write log entry to journal info.
          : 	string	if verbose() enabled, write string/s to stdout.
   Example: msg.sys "Sir. There's something I think you should know."
    Source: /usr/share/okusi/entities/entities.d/files/lockfiles.bash
#-Function--msg.sys-----------------------------------------------------------
